1
00:00:01,035 --> 00:00:02,136
- ANDY AND LESLIE
SENT US CARE PACKAGES.

2
00:00:02,170 --> 00:00:04,405
- "HEY, BEN, JUST A FEW THINGS
TO REMIND YOU OF HOME.

3
00:00:04,438 --> 00:00:05,439
LOVE, LESLIE."

4
00:00:05,473 --> 00:00:07,241
AH, WAFFLE MIX.

5
00:00:07,275 --> 00:00:08,742
JJ's DINER MUG.

6
00:00:08,776 --> 00:00:10,711
NEW PAJAMAS.

7
00:00:10,744 --> 00:00:13,081
WOW, THERE'S A LOT
OF STUFF IN HERE.

8
00:00:13,114 --> 00:00:15,649
"BOX 1 OF 12"?

9
00:00:15,683 --> 00:00:18,452
- "APRIL, HERE'S SOMETHING
TO HELP YOU REMEMBER

10
00:00:18,486 --> 00:00:20,488
OUR THREE-LEGGED DOG
CHAMPION."

11
00:00:20,521 --> 00:00:21,422
- AH, THAT'S CUTE.

12
00:00:21,455 --> 00:00:23,091
- "ALSO, YOU ARE WAY BETTER
AT LAUNDRY.

13
00:00:23,124 --> 00:00:25,593
"CAN YOU PLEASE DO MINE
AND SEND IT BACK TO ME?

14
00:00:25,626 --> 00:00:28,362
THANKS. LOVE YOU.
MOUSE RAT RULES. LOVE, ANDY."

15
00:00:28,396 --> 00:00:29,463
- LESS CUTE.

16
00:00:29,497 --> 00:00:30,698
- "P.S. PLEASE HURRY.

17
00:00:30,731 --> 00:00:32,400
"I'VE BEEN WEARING
A BANDANA AS UNDERWEAR

18
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:33,401
FOR THREE DAYS NOW."

19
00:00:33,434 --> 00:00:35,069
LOOK, THERE'S A PICTURE.

20
00:00:35,103 --> 00:00:37,705
- AH!
THAT'S HORRIFYING.

21
00:00:37,738 --> 00:00:40,608
- [sighs]

22
00:00:40,641 --> 00:00:42,776
I LOVE HIM SO MUCH.

23
00:00:42,810 --> 00:00:45,779
[triumphant music]

24
00:00:45,813 --> 00:00:53,821
*

25
00:01:03,231 --> 00:01:05,433
- OKAY, SO DO YOU HAVE
THE RESULTS OF THE STUDY?

26
00:01:05,466 --> 00:01:06,667
- YES, AND THEY'RE GREAT.

27
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:08,369
YOUR TAX ON SODA

28
00:01:08,402 --> 00:01:10,471
WOULD DEFINITELY
LOWER DIABETES IN THIS TOWN.

29
00:01:10,504 --> 00:01:12,640
OH, AND I HAVE A GREAT PROP
FOR THE MEETING.

30
00:01:12,673 --> 00:01:14,275
THIS IS THE AMOUNT OF SUGAR

31
00:01:14,308 --> 00:01:16,277
THAT THE AVERAGE PAWNEE
10-YEAR-OLD CONSUMES,

32
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:18,479
FROM SODA, EVERY MONTH.

33
00:01:18,512 --> 00:01:19,680
- THAT IS GROSS.
- IT'S GROSS.

34
00:01:19,713 --> 00:01:21,682
- ALL THAT SUGAR?
- IT'S REALLY GROSS.

35
00:01:21,715 --> 00:01:23,484
- WHAT A POWERFUL IMAGE.
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

36
00:01:23,517 --> 00:01:24,718
- WHAT DID YOU PUT IN THE SUGAR?
IT'S SO GOOD.

37
00:01:24,752 --> 00:01:26,720
MY FIRST ACT
AS A CITY COUNCILWOMAN--

38
00:01:26,754 --> 00:01:29,623
I'VE PROPOSED A TAX ON
ALL THOSE GIANT SUGARY SODAS

39
00:01:29,657 --> 00:01:31,692
SO WE CAN DISCOURAGE PEOPLE
FROM DRINKING THEM.

40
00:01:31,725 --> 00:01:33,294
I BELIEVE, WITH MY HELP,

41
00:01:33,327 --> 00:01:35,196
ALL LOCAL RESTAURANTS
CAN GET HEALTHIER--

42
00:01:35,229 --> 00:01:37,698
PAUNCH BURGER, BIG AND WIDE,
THE FAT SACK,

43
00:01:37,731 --> 00:01:39,633
CORONEL PLUM'S SLOP TROUGH--

44
00:01:39,667 --> 00:01:41,635
WHICH WAS FORMERLY
SUE'S SALADS

45
00:01:41,669 --> 00:01:44,372
UNTIL WE RAN THAT
OUT OF TOWN.

46
00:01:45,339 --> 00:01:46,674
- AH, COUNCILWOMAN.

47
00:01:46,707 --> 00:01:48,442
IN HONOR OF
YOUR NEVER-ENDING QUEST

48
00:01:48,476 --> 00:01:50,178
TO PERSONALLY BABYSIT

49
00:01:50,211 --> 00:01:51,745
EACH AND EVERY
AMERICAN CITIZEN,

50
00:01:51,779 --> 00:01:54,448
I WENT TO PAUNCH BURGER
AND GOT MYSELF A NUMBER TWO--

51
00:01:54,482 --> 00:01:57,518
DOUBLE BACON GRENADE DELUXE,
HASH BROWNS,

52
00:01:57,551 --> 00:01:59,720
CHILI CHEESE FRIES,
AND ONE POACHED EGG.

53
00:01:59,753 --> 00:02:01,722
- UGH!
NUMBER TWO IS RIGHT.

54
00:02:01,755 --> 00:02:04,758
- I ALSO PICKED UP A 64-OUNCE
SWEETUMS SUGAR SPLASH.

55
00:02:04,792 --> 00:02:06,594
DAMN IT, I LOVE THIS COUNTRY
SO MUCH.

56
00:02:06,627 --> 00:02:09,297
- RON, I'M REALLY GLAD
THAT YOU'RE HERE.

57
00:02:09,330 --> 00:02:11,265
OUR POLITICAL DIFFERENCES
ASIDE,

58
00:02:11,299 --> 00:02:13,434
I AM ABOUT TO GO TO
MY FIRST COMMITTEE MEETING

59
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:16,704
AS A CITY COUNCILWOMAN.

60
00:02:16,737 --> 00:02:18,406
THERE'S SOMETHING
I NEED TO SAY TO YOU.

61
00:02:18,439 --> 00:02:19,640
- PLEASE DON'T.

62
00:02:19,673 --> 00:02:21,375
- I KNOW YOU HATE
FEELINGS AND EMOTIONS,

63
00:02:21,409 --> 00:02:23,477
BUT I WOULD NOT BE WHERE I AM
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU.

64
00:02:23,511 --> 00:02:26,280
YOU HIRED ME.
YOU'VE ALWAYS SUPPORTED ME.

65
00:02:26,314 --> 00:02:27,715
HOW CAN I EVER REPAY YOU?

66
00:02:27,748 --> 00:02:29,183
- [slurps]

67
00:02:29,217 --> 00:02:30,384
GET ME A REFILL.

68
00:02:32,786 --> 00:02:34,555
- HEY, EVERYBODY.

69
00:02:34,588 --> 00:02:36,290
SO, I'VE BEEN GOING
OVER YOUR REPORTS.

70
00:02:36,324 --> 00:02:40,361
LET'S TRY TO BE CONSISTENT
WITH OUR FONTS, GUYS, OKAY?

71
00:02:40,394 --> 00:02:41,595
THERE'S A CRAZY AMOUNT

72
00:02:41,629 --> 00:02:44,432
OF RANDOM FONT DIFFERENCES
IN THESE MEMOS.

73
00:02:44,465 --> 00:02:47,601
- YEAH, PEOPLE.
CONSISTENT FONT USAGE. COME ON.

74
00:02:47,635 --> 00:02:50,304
- TIMES NEW ROMAN,
ACROSS THE BOARD.

75
00:02:50,338 --> 00:02:53,674
NO GENEVA, NO GARAMOND,
DEFINITELY NO PAPYRUS.

76
00:02:53,707 --> 00:02:55,376
- PAPYRUS?
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

77
00:02:55,409 --> 00:02:57,745
THERE'S NO PLACE FOR THAT IN
A PROFESSIONAL OFFICE SETTING.

78
00:02:57,778 --> 00:02:59,447
- YES!
THANK YOU, APRIL.

79
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:03,717
THESE COLLEGE INTERNS REALLY
NEED TO BE WHIPPED INTO SHAPE,

80
00:03:03,751 --> 00:03:06,487
BUT DON'T WORRY, BECAUSE
THEY CALL ME DEVO,

81
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,789
'CAUSE I CAN
"WHIP 'EM GOOD."

82
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:13,794
AND OBVIOUSLY MAKE SURE
THE CONTENT'S PERFECT TOO.

83
00:03:13,827 --> 00:03:16,664
OH, AND, UH, 12 POINT.

84
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:19,767
13'S JUST OBNOXIOUS.
GREAT MEETING.

85
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,669
- OUT OF THE WAY, PEOPLE.

86
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:23,537
MOTIVATIONAL BRIGADE
COMING THROUGH.

87
00:03:23,571 --> 00:03:25,339
- HO HO!

88
00:03:25,373 --> 00:03:27,975
- SO, YOU BOYS ARE GONNA GO
WORK OUT TOGETHER, HUH?

89
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:31,312
NICE. WHEREABOUTS?
- COMMUNITY COLLEGE.

90
00:03:31,345 --> 00:03:32,480
- EH, THAT'S TOO FAR.

91
00:03:32,513 --> 00:03:34,482
- CHRIS AND TOM OFFERED
TO HELP ME TRAIN

92
00:03:34,515 --> 00:03:35,949
TO BECOME A POLICE OFFICER.

93
00:03:35,983 --> 00:03:39,353
THE PHYSICAL EXAM IS
ABOUT THREE MONTHS AWAY

94
00:03:39,387 --> 00:03:46,460
AND I AM IN TERRIBLE SHAPE,
BUT I CAN ALREADY DO THIS...

95
00:03:46,494 --> 00:03:48,929
SO, I'M GETTING THERE.

96
00:03:48,962 --> 00:03:50,030
SO, I'VE GOT
A LIST OF EVERYTHING

97
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,098
THAT I'M SUPPOSED TO
BE ABLE TO DO

98
00:03:51,131 --> 00:03:53,367
TO GET INTO THE POLICE ACADEMY,
AND NUMBER ONE IS,

99
00:03:53,401 --> 00:03:56,504
"BE ABLE TO RUN 2 MILES
IN UNDER 25 MINUTES."

100
00:03:56,537 --> 00:03:57,705
THAT'S A TYPO, RIGHT?

101
00:03:57,738 --> 00:03:58,806
I MEAN,
THAT'S HUMANLY IMPOSSIBLE.

102
00:03:58,839 --> 00:04:01,642
- WHEN YOU ARE ABLE TO FOCUS
YOUR MIND AND YOUR BODY,

103
00:04:01,675 --> 00:04:03,511
ANYTHING IS POSSIBLE.

104
00:04:03,544 --> 00:04:06,980
- ANYTHING IS POSSIBLE!

105
00:04:07,014 --> 00:04:08,849
- MS. PINEWOOD,

106
00:04:08,882 --> 00:04:10,718
RECENTLY, MANY OF
THE LOCAL RESTAURANTS

107
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:13,654
HAVE CHANGED THEIR
"SMALL-SIZE" OPTION

108
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:16,524
TO A WHOPPING 64-OUNCES.

109
00:04:16,557 --> 00:04:18,792
- THAT'S CORRECT, AND IT'S
GREAT FOR THE CONSUMER.

110
00:04:18,826 --> 00:04:20,428
MORE BANG FOR THE BUCK.

111
00:04:20,461 --> 00:04:22,530
ARE WE PUTTING BARGAINS
ON TRIAL HERE?

112
00:04:22,563 --> 00:04:24,732
- HOW COULD ANY SANE PERSON
CALL THAT "SMALL"?

113
00:04:24,765 --> 00:04:26,834
- WELL, IF THE CUSTOMER
TRULY WANTS A SMALLER SIZE,

114
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:28,001
THERE IS AN OPTION.

115
00:04:28,035 --> 00:04:30,871
- OH, DO YOU MEAN
THE "LI'L SWALLOW"?

116
00:04:30,904 --> 00:04:32,773
DOES ANYBODY BUY THAT?

117
00:04:32,806 --> 00:04:33,974
- SOME GIRLS BUY THEM
FOR THEIR DOLLHOUSES,

118
00:04:34,007 --> 00:04:35,776
BUT THEY'RE NOT
VERY POPULAR.

119
00:04:35,809 --> 00:04:37,478
I MEAN, FOR ONLY
A NICKEL MORE,

120
00:04:37,511 --> 00:04:38,979
YOU GET 64 OUNCES.

121
00:04:39,012 --> 00:04:42,883
- WELL, UH, PAUNCH BURGER
JUST RECENTLY CAME OUT

122
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:47,388
WITH A NEW 128-OUNCE OPTION.

123
00:04:47,421 --> 00:04:49,790
MOST PEOPLE CALL IT
A GALLON,

124
00:04:49,823 --> 00:04:50,824
BUT THEY CALL IT
THE "REGULAR."

125
00:04:50,858 --> 00:04:54,962
THEN, THERE IS A HORRIFYING
512-OUNCE VERSION

126
00:04:54,995 --> 00:04:57,698
THAT THE CALL "CHILD SIZE."

127
00:04:57,731 --> 00:05:00,768
HOW IS THIS
A "CHILD-SIZE SODA"?

128
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,537
- WELL, IT'S ROUGHLY THE SIZE
OF A TWO-YEAR-OLD CHILD,

129
00:05:03,571 --> 00:05:04,838
IF THE CHILD WERE LIQUEFIED.

130
00:05:04,872 --> 00:05:07,441
IT'S A REAL BARGAIN
AT $1.59.

131
00:05:07,475 --> 00:05:08,709
- I'M SORRY, MS. PINEWOOD,

132
00:05:08,742 --> 00:05:10,444
BUT WHY WOULD ANYBODY
NEED THIS MUCH SODA?

133
00:05:10,478 --> 00:05:12,613
- IT'S NOT MY PLACE TO SPEAK
FOR THE CONSUMER,

134
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:15,649
BUT EVERYONE SHOULD BUY IT.

135
00:05:15,683 --> 00:05:17,718
- COME ON, ANDY, COME ON.
YOU CAN DO IT.

136
00:05:17,751 --> 00:05:19,052
GO, GO, GO, GO,
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO.

137
00:05:19,086 --> 00:05:21,121
DIG, DIG, DIG, DIG, DIG,
DIG, DIG, DIG, DIG.

138
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:22,656
- AAH!
- YES!

139
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:23,824
- OH, MY GOD.

140
00:05:23,857 --> 00:05:26,727
IT'S SO HOT.
IT WAS HORRIBLE.

141
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:29,930
OH, I'M GOING TO DIE.
I'M SO TIRED.

142
00:05:29,963 --> 00:05:32,666
[groans]
EVERYTHING HURTS.

143
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:34,968
RUNNING IS IMPOSSIBLE.
[groans]

144
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:36,737
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

145
00:05:36,770 --> 00:05:39,039
- TOM, NOW IS NOT THE TIME
FOR CRITICISM.

146
00:05:39,072 --> 00:05:40,307
HOW DID HE DO?

147
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:43,777
- ANDY FINISHED HIS TWO-MILE RUN
IN 29 MINUTES AND 43 SECONDS.

148
00:05:43,811 --> 00:05:47,415
- NO! I'M NEVER
GONNA BE A COP.

149
00:05:47,448 --> 00:05:48,849
I'M GONNA HAVE TO BE
A ROBBER.

150
00:05:48,882 --> 00:05:50,518
- OH, COME ON.
HANG IN THERE, PAL.

151
00:05:50,551 --> 00:05:51,919
I'M GONNA DRIVE AROUND.

152
00:05:51,952 --> 00:05:55,789
- [groans]
- ANDY, I'M PROUD OF YOU.

153
00:05:55,823 --> 00:05:58,125
NOT BECAUSE OF WHAT YOU DID,
WHICH WAS TERRIBLE,

154
00:05:58,158 --> 00:06:01,094
BUT BECAUSE OF WHAT I'M GOING TO
BE ABLE TO GET YOU TO DO.

155
00:06:01,128 --> 00:06:02,763
I GUESS I'M PROUD OF ME.

156
00:06:02,796 --> 00:06:03,731
- THANKS, MAN.
ME TOO.

157
00:06:03,764 --> 00:06:06,400
- WE HAVE SO MUCH WORK TO DO.

158
00:06:06,434 --> 00:06:07,801
- OH, HEY, ELLIS,

159
00:06:07,835 --> 00:06:09,570
HAVE YOU PUT THE CAMPAIGN
PICTURES UP ON THE WEBSITE?

160
00:06:09,603 --> 00:06:13,507
- OH. YEAH.
I STARTED DOING THEM.

161
00:06:13,541 --> 00:06:16,710
- AND ARE YOU GOING TO
FINISH DOING THEM?

162
00:06:16,744 --> 00:06:19,847
- OH.
LATER, MAN.

163
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:23,083
- [sighs]

164
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:28,489
- I ACTUALLY THINK
YOU LOOK REALLY GOOD,

165
00:06:28,522 --> 00:06:31,091
EXCEPT FOR THE STICK
UP YOUR BUTT.

166
00:06:31,124 --> 00:06:32,693
- WHO DO YOU THINK DREW IT?

167
00:06:32,726 --> 00:06:34,695
WAS IT NATHANIEL?
ELLIS?

168
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:36,664
MAN, I FEEL LIKE
THESE INTERNS

169
00:06:36,697 --> 00:06:39,166
DO NOT RESPECT
OR LIKE ME AT ALL.

170
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:41,168
- HONESTLY, YOU COULD
LOOSEN UP A BIT

171
00:06:41,201 --> 00:06:42,636
ON THE FONT STUFF.

172
00:06:42,670 --> 00:06:45,573
- [sighs]
- AND EVERYTHING IN GENERAL.

173
00:06:45,606 --> 00:06:47,174
- GOD, THIS IS INSANE.
THEY'RE INTERNS.

174
00:06:47,207 --> 00:06:50,077
THEY'RE TOTALLY REPLACEABLE,
AND I'M THEIR BOSS.

175
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:52,680
JUST FIRE THEM.

176
00:06:52,713 --> 00:06:54,181
- UH, HEY, JEN.

177
00:06:54,214 --> 00:06:56,750
LISTEN, I'M HAVING A PROBLEM
WITH SOME OF THE INTERNS.

178
00:06:56,784 --> 00:06:58,719
I'M THINKING OF
MAKING SOME CHANGES.

179
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:00,721
YEAH.

180
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:04,458
TURNS OUT ELLIS IS
CONGRESSMAN MURRAY'S NEPHEW.

181
00:07:04,492 --> 00:07:07,695
NATHANIEL IS RELATED
TO DONALD RUMSFELD.

182
00:07:07,728 --> 00:07:09,830
BRITTANY'S DAD IS
BEN BERNANKE'S DENTIST.

183
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:11,765
EVERY SINGLE ONE
OF THESE LITTLE TWERPS

184
00:07:11,799 --> 00:07:13,133
IS SERIOUSLY CONNECTED.

185
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:14,668
SO, NEW PLAN.

186
00:07:14,702 --> 00:07:17,505
INSTEAD OF FIRING THEM,

187
00:07:17,538 --> 00:07:20,774
I AM GOING TO KISS
THEIR ASSES LIKE CRAZY.

188
00:07:20,808 --> 00:07:24,144
- MS. KNOPE, THIS IS ABOUT
CONSUMER RIGHTS,

189
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:26,747
AND IF THEY DON'T WANT TO
DRINK OUR DELICIOUS SODAS,

190
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:29,783
WE DO PROVIDE HEALTHIER
OPTIONS, LIKE WATER ZERO.

191
00:07:29,817 --> 00:07:32,152
- OH, YES. LET'S TALK
ABOUT WATER ZERO.

192
00:07:32,185 --> 00:07:34,788
THE NAME IMPLIES THAT
THERE ARE ZERO CALORIES,

193
00:07:34,822 --> 00:07:37,491
LIKE MOST WATER,
BUT IN FACT,

194
00:07:37,525 --> 00:07:39,693
IT HAS 300 CALORIES
PER SERVING.

195
00:07:39,727 --> 00:07:41,695
ISN'T THAT MISLEADING?

196
00:07:41,729 --> 00:07:42,830
- THE ZERO ON THE LABEL

197
00:07:42,863 --> 00:07:43,964
REFERS TO THE AMOUNT
OF WATER IN IT,

198
00:07:43,997 --> 00:07:45,098
WHICH IS ZERO.

199
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:47,935
IF YOU WANT
ZERO-CALORIE WATER,

200
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:49,737
TRY DIET WATER ZERO LITE.

201
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:51,505
IT HAS ONLY 60 CALORIES.

202
00:07:51,539 --> 00:07:52,673
- OKAY, I THINK
WE'RE DONE HERE.

203
00:07:52,706 --> 00:07:53,807
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

204
00:07:53,841 --> 00:07:56,510
- OH, COUNCILWOMAN,
ONE MORE THING.

205
00:07:56,544 --> 00:07:58,712
IF YOUR TAX BILL PASSES,

206
00:07:58,746 --> 00:08:00,781
LOCAL RESTAURANTS
WILL HURT BADLY.

207
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:02,816
WE'LL HAVE TO LAY OFF
ABOUT 100 PEOPLE.

208
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:05,586
- YOU'RE BLUFFING.
SHE'S BLUFFING.

209
00:08:05,619 --> 00:08:07,054
ARE YOU BLUFFING?

210
00:08:07,087 --> 00:08:08,956
- THE SECOND
YOUR TAX BILL PASSES,

211
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:12,860
THIS PRESS RELEASE
GOES WIDE.

212
00:08:12,893 --> 00:08:14,662
SEE YOU AT THE MEETING.

213
00:08:14,695 --> 00:08:18,832
- "LESLIE KNOPE SODA TAX
FORCES MASSIVE LAYOFFS."

214
00:08:18,866 --> 00:08:20,534
OH, MY GOD, ANN.
I NEED SOME SUGAR.

215
00:08:20,568 --> 00:08:21,869
- NO, NO. NO, NO, NO!
STOP IT!

216
00:08:21,902 --> 00:08:23,737
LESLIE, YOU STOP IT
RIGHT NOW!

217
00:08:25,606 --> 00:08:27,074
- OKAY, LET'S GET STARTED.

218
00:08:27,107 --> 00:08:28,008
I PROPOSED THIS BILL,

219
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:29,910
BUT THE ISSUE HAS BECOME
VERY COMPLICATED,

220
00:08:29,943 --> 00:08:32,145
SO BEFORE I DECIDE HOW
I AM GOING TO VOTE,

221
00:08:32,179 --> 00:08:33,847
I'D LOVE TO HEAR
FROM BOTH SIDES.

222
00:08:33,881 --> 00:08:34,948
WHO'D LIKE TO START?
YES.

223
00:08:34,982 --> 00:08:36,617
- YEAH, I WORK
AT COLONEL PLUMP'S,

224
